## COMPILATION ERROR ANALYSIS

### Error Categories:

#### 1. Room Database Mapping Issues (@MapColumn required)
- FCMTokenDao.kt:127 - Map<String, Integer> return type
- NotificationQueueDao.kt:212 - Map<String, Integer> return type  
- NotificationMuteDao.kt:282 - Map<String, Integer> return type
- NotificationHistoryDao.kt:187 - Map<String, Integer> return type
- NotificationHistoryDao.kt:195 - Map<String, Integer> return type

#### 2. Room Column Name Mismatch 
- NotificationPreferenceDao.kt:240 - QuietHoursSettings field mapping
  - Query columns: quiet_hours_enabled, quiet_hours_start, quiet_hours_end
  - Class fields: quietHoursEnabled, quietHoursStart, quietHoursEnd

#### 3. Foreign Key Index Warnings (Performance, not errors)
- PostCommentEntity.kt, PostLikeEntity.kt, SavedPostEntity.kt, NotificationMuteEntity.kt

## Root Cause Analysis:
The errors are from the SPEC-20250113-notifications-privacy implementation. The new DAO queries returning Map<String, Integer> are missing @MapColumn annotations to tell Room how to map query result columns to the Map keys/values.

## Fix Strategy:
1. Add @MapColumn annotations to all Map-returning queries
2. Fix field name mapping in QuietHoursSettings data class
3. Address foreign key index warnings (optional performance improvement)